description.text: Submodel containing techical data to the asset.
General information refers to the basic details about a product that would identify and describe it without getting into the detailed technical specifications.
A unique identifier assigned to a product by the manufacturer for inventory control and ordering purposes.
A unique identifier assigned to a stock item in a warehouse or inventory management system.
The area of the air damper.
The length of the cable attached to the air damper.
The level of protection provided by the air damper against solid particles and liquids.
The temperature range within which the air damper can operate.
The dimensions of the air damper in the order of width, height, and depth.
The switch that is used to control the air damper.

A technical property generally refers to a characteristic or attribute that defines or describes the technical aspects of an object, system, material, or process. These properties are usually measurable or quantifiable and are critical in determining how something will function or perform in a specific context.
The force applied to the air damper to rotate it.
The maximum rotation angle of the air damper.
The power consumed by the air damper.
The time taken for the air damper to reach its position.
The signal required to position the air damper.
The temperature range of the medium that the air damper can handle.
The maximum relative humidity within which the air damper can operate without failure.
The voltage required to operate the air damper.
